03/02/2011
ANKARA, Turkey -- President Abdullah Gul and his Nigerian counterpart Goodluck Jonathan agreed on Wednesday (February 2nd) to ramp up economic bilateral co-operation.
"We determined jointly that there are many opportunities in the economic field ...
Our trade [volume] has reached nearly $1 billion but Nigeria holds great investment opportunities," Gul said after talks with Jonathan in Ankara.
They signed agreements to co-operate in the fields of defence, tourism, education and investment promotion.
(AFP, Hurriyet, Anadolu news agency - 02/02/11)
